<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="warn-vt">warn <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /wɔːn/    美 /wɔːrn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>警告；告诫；提醒：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I tried to warn him, but he wouldn’t listen.
我试图警告过他，但他不听。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>warn (sb) about / of sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She warned us about / of the serious situation.
她提醒我们要注意严峻的局势。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>warn (sb) against(doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He warned us against pickpockets.
他提醒我们要提防扒手。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>warn sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We warned them not to skate on such thin ice.
我们告诫过他们,不要在那么薄的冰上溜冰。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>warn sb + that / wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Scientists <strong>warn that</strong> global warming will cause catastrophic climate changes.
科学家警告说全球变暖将导致灾难性的气候变化。</p><footer>北师大新必修③-8</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>My father warned me <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ going to the West Coast because it was crowded with tourists.  （2010 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. against  </p></div>